    "title": "体验至上的“大胆放弃”",
    "page_range": "1",
    "summary": "This section answers questions regarding game design trade-offs, player retention strategies, and engagement mechanics in 《燕云十六声》.\n- **Topics/Questions:** Why abandon industry-standard daily task systems? How to sustain player engagement without them? How to shift player motivation from extrinsic to intrinsic drivers?\n- **Entities:** 《燕云十六声》 (game title), 每日任务 (Daily Tasks), 奇遇系统 (Encounter System), 点点数据 (research source).\n- **Definitions/Concepts:** Daily tasks as conventional DAU/retention tools; encounters as high-quality, freely explorable content designed to replace repetitive grinding.\n- **Claims:** Removing daily tasks eliminates player login anxiety but may sacrifice short-term retention metrics; replacing them with continuous main/side quests and exploration-driven content attracts immersion-focused players; successfully shifts engagement from extrinsic numerical rewards to intrinsic motivation.\n- **Metrics:** DAU (日活), user retention (用户留存), short-term goal pursuit.\n- **Evidence Type:** Independent industry research and analysis (点点数据自主研究及绘制).\n- **Dates/Procedures/Tables/Figures:** Not specified in this excerpt."
