    "page_range": "1",
    "summary": "This section outlines the design framework and post-launch operational strategy of the game 《杖剑传说》, enabling retrieval for queries regarding:\n- **Topics & Core Concepts:** The “放置为表、MMO为里” (idle surface, MMO core) design philosophy; integration of vertical idle mechanics with MMORPG depth; IP collaboration strategy targeting core ACG audiences.\n- **Entities:** Game: 《杖剑传说》; Collaborated IPs: 蔬菜精灵, 为美好的世界献上祝福, 洛天依, 言和, 罗小黑战记2; Data Source: 点点数据.\n- **Dates & Timelines:** Collaboration frequency (~every 2 months); specific rollout milestones: launch (同步), 2 months, 4 months, and 6 months post-public beta (公测).\n- **Definitions & Mechanics:** “半即时指令队列” (semi-real-time command queue); “BD构建” (build/strategy construction via skill combos & equipment affixes); “大佬带本”文化 (veteran-led dungeon grouping); pure 2D fresh art style.\n- **Procedures & Systems:** Pre-configuring 8 active/passive skills; forming skill/equipment synergies; solo idle progression vs. team-dependent high-yield dungeons; guild-based social engagement.\n- **Claims:** The hybrid model significantly lowers daily participation barriers while ensuring long-term playability through hundreds of skill combinations; MMO-style social collaboration and guilds are critical drivers for player retention and revenue; the 2D art style enables high compatibility with ACG IPs, facilitating rapid content deployment and effective fan conversion.\n- **Figures/Tables & Metrics:** A timeline figure/chart documenting four major IP collaborations within the first six months post-launch; metrics include ~2-month collaboration intervals, 8-skill loadout capacity, and hundreds of total available skills.\n- **Evidence Types:** Gameplay system analysis, operational timeline data, and third-party market research (点点数据自主研究及绘制)."
